line_1: Yet demme if a soul will do't —
line_2: And plight my faith and gold to-boot;

line_1: A Shell, a Butter-fly can do't.
line_2: A Print, a Bronze, a Flow'r, a Root,

line_1: The swap we yet will do't;
line_2: Thou'se get the saul o' boot.

line_1: Nothing but hopes of Heaven should make me do't:
line_2: Sure 't was no earthly Gain that charm'd you to't,

line_1: And if physic can cure her — I know yours will do't.
line_2: Says Colin, your judgment there's none can dispute;

line_1: Quoth I, "With a' my heart, I'll do't;
line_2: "An' meet you on the holy spot;

line_1: And tho' some Malicious Young Spirit did do't,
line_2: You may know by the Hand, it had no Cloven Foot.
